  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2012-01-24",
    "date": "2012-02-24T23:06:49Z",
    "text": "Health Freedom for Seniors Act - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow tax-free transfers of required distributions after age 70 1/2 from an individual retirement account (IRA) and other tax-exempt retirement accounts to a health savings account.\u00a0 Exempts such transfers from the excise tax on excess contributions to tax-favored accounts and annuities."
